3. **Trading decisions when there are trades available in the market**:

{% if not public_information.market_state.median_prices[0] and not public_information.market_state.median_prices[1] %}

- No trades have been made yet.

{% else %}

- When median price of Project  >  median price of No Project, then do nothing
- When median price of Project  < median price of No Project, then increase the median price of the Project market or decrease the median price of No Project market

Increasing the median price of the Project market can be done in two ways:
    - if the best bid is higher than the median price in the Project market, you can accept the best bid in this market by sending an ask with the now option set to true.
    - if the best bid is lower than the median price in the Project market, you can create a bid in the No Project market that is 10% above the median price in the No Project market

Decreasing the median price in the No Project market can be done in two ways:
    - if the best ask is lower than the median price in the No Project market, you can accept the best ask in this market by sending a bid with the now option set to true.
    - if the best ask is higher than the median price in the No Project market, you can create a bid in the No Project market that is 10% below the median price in the No Project market


{% endif %}


