       "order": {
           "id": <order_id>,
           "condition": <0 or 1>
       },
   }

   C. Do nothing:
   {}

Remember:
- You can only trade one share at a time
- If a median price does not exist yet, it is assumed to be 0
- when deciding between several offers to accept, select the order with the smallest difference between your private signal and the median price
- when deciding between several offers to make, select the order with the smallest difference between your private signal and the median price
- when choosing what market to target, manipulating the losing market is cheaper. So manipulte the losing market unless the offer you intend to make resembles existing open offers in this market.
- You have limited time to trade
- Setting "now": true will execute at the best available price
- Orders can be canceled before they are fulfilled
- setting the condition to 1 means that the order is for No Project development
- setting the condition to 0 means that the order is for Project development
- your goal is to make sure the median price of the Project Market is above the median price of the No Project Market
